title: For Sale:  Savage Precision 10 Bolt Action 308 Sniper Rifle w/ Millett 4-16 Scope
postcontent:
This is a Savage Precision 10 Bolt Action Rifle with a 20" medium profile barrel that is finished off with a high quality compensator / muzzle break to help tame the bark of the 308 round.  

The rifle action has the Savage Accutrigger which is super light and breaks like glass.  To further aid accuracy, the barrel is free floated into the Savage Accustock to isolate it as much as possible.  

Up top is a Millett TRS-1 4x-16x scope with Mil Dot Reticle.  It has a generous 30 mm tube to collect tons of light to keep the sight picture bright in all types of conditions.  It is mounted on a one piece weaver rail that is rock solid to hold zero after use.  

In addition to the factory 4 round mag, I have (2) of the 10 round Dark Eagle Custom high capacity mags.  These function nicely and give that extra capacity for shooting at the range or in the field.  To help steady your shots, there is also a nice adjustable bipod attached to the front sling point.  

To finish off the package, I have everything tucked away nicely in a Plano GunGuard hard sided case.  There are five every secure latch closures.  Two of the latches have built in key locks. title: For Sale/Trade:  1974 Honda Trail 90 - CT90 - Needs Nothing! Street Legal Daily Rider!
postcontent:
Up for sale is my Honda Trail 90. I've put a lot of time into cleaning this bike up and getting all the little issues taken care of. I watch these on Craigslist all the time and its amazing how much people ask for hashed out bikes with no title, no street legal kit and barely running engines. This bike isn't going to win any shows or awards but I wanted to make it into the cleanest daily ridden CT90 you're going to find.

Cosmetically it has all the checking, spots, nicks and scratches that a 41 year old trail bike is going to have. I've scrubbed and polished the chrome, most of which is in really great shape. I re-taped the seat cover because the original tape job was crumbling. The plastics are a little rough, but they're all there. Overall this is one of the nicer CT90s that I've ridden. Fully street legal with working headlight, brake light, tail light and turn signals. Comes with the original toolkit as well as the locking extra gas can.

Mechanically it is a very strong runner. Typically starts first kick with no choke and runs strong until you shut it off. Shifts into first very strong with no slipping and shifts extremely well through all the gears. Recent valve and point adjustments, along with a brand new spark plug. Has plenty of 90cc power through all 4 gears. Throttle is responsive with no bogging/flooding. Transmission feels strong and grippy in both high and low. Suspension is a little soft for my tastes, but if you plan on a lot of trail riding you may like it that way. Rear tire is fairly new and front tire is brand spanking new. This is a solid, reliable daily rider.

I have the clean Oregon title in my name. Tags are good until December 2016. Comes with an Oregon Off Road permit that is good into 2017. Two keys. This bike literally needs nothing to be a legal daily rider on or off road. 4000 miles and plenty of life left. People on the internet regularly post about their 90 turning over the odometer. Treat these bikes well and they will always start first kick and run forever.

I'll consider throwing in the matching vintage cooler and cargo net if you don't low ball me.
